Operatives of the Delta State Police Command and the vigilante have arrested three suspected child traffickers in the state. The suspects identified as Ado-Obi Oguguo ‘f’ (38yrs), Chidima Osita age (36yrs), and Nkirnka Ikechukwu ‘f’ (30yrs) are residents of Omerigboma Village, Oko, Oshimili South, Delta State. They were arrested based on a petition written to the Area Commander, Asaba on behalf of victim of child trafficking (name withheld),16 years, a native of Izza North LGA of Ebonyi State, who was to be taken to Onicha-Ugbo for prostitution. The Delta State Police Command led by CP Ari Muhammed Ali confirmed the report in a statement signed by the Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe. He said, “Preliminary investigation revealed that suspects were into prostitution, and on 22/6/2022, they arranged for a girl named Chidima surname unknown age 16yrs to be taken to Mali for prostitution.” “investigation is ongoing and effort to arrest other members of the syndicate is ongoing,” he added. 